  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support Pacific Communities Advocacy for COP 23</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">With Fiji confirmed as the President of the 23rd UN Climate Talks in Bonn, Germany, the Pacific region as a whole has the opportunity to show the world what true climate leadership looks like. This means highlighting the threat of climate change in the Pacific, and calling on the global community to halt this threat by committing to a global moratorium on all fossil fuel development, a rapid and just transition to 100% renewable energy, and support for impacted communities who are already suffering the worst effects of climate change.

Through our connection to 350.org Pacific, we are working alongside an alliance of partners in the Pacific to ensure that we are well organised and coordinated to support leaders and CSOs going into COP 23. We are also working hard to ensure that while we have solid representation in this important international space and we are organizing with our frontline communities on the ground, to carry out mobilisations in and around the Pacific during COP 23.</narrative>
  </description>
